    "Combined with literature estimates -MoE estimated at (∼ 2×), improved datasets at (∼ 3×), and tokenizers at (∼ 1.6×) -this totals 60.3×, well under 100×.",
    "This contrasts sharply with Ho et al. [2024]'s estimate of 22, 000 efficiency gains the last decade, leaving an apparent gap of 350× or more.However, this discrepancy resolves when accounting for scale-dependent innovations.",
    "Extrapolating our measured scaling exponents to the 2023 frontier compute budgets (1.3×10 22 FLOPs), the LSTM to Kaplan Transformer transition alone accounts for 725× of the efficiency gains.",
    "Combined with the Chinchilla rebalancing gains of 3.7× and 2.6× for scale-invariant innovations, we estimate total efficiency gains of approximately 6, 930×, substantially closing the gap with literature estimates over the same time period.",
    "Further, our extrapolated estimates of LSTM to transformer efficiency gain in 2017 are around 91×."
